{
  "stem": "15962.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We left Mauthausen and walked down from the high ground, where the stone fortress enclosing the camp stood, towards the city that sits on the banks of the Danube.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We walked through the town early one morning and were surprised at the total-- not just the indifference of the population but the expression of hatred towards us and the feeling that this is right.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All of these prisoners are dangerous animals and should be exterminated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We walked to the railway station, which was actually quite a distance, especially for people who were hungry and not in good physical condition.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were shipped to a relatively small distance along the Danube, to a town called Melk, which is the seat of a beautiful Benedictine monastery that served as a major hospital during the war.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The camp that we walked to from the railway station was on the opposite hill of this monastery.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Normal in comparison with ours, I mean this was towards the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, anybody in his normal mind should have realized that the war was lost.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But Austrians were sympathetic to the Nazi cause and didn't feel anything wrong, seeing us treated in the way that the guards did.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That we-- once we were in the camp, we were--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was a work camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Most of the men-- these were almost exclusively men.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't remember any women.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Although some of the history claims that there were some.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't remember any.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nearby were underground factories for ammunitions that were hulled out in the-- in the mountainside, so that they would be better protected from air raids.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the factories and the-- the caves were all built by the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
